A N A C T
RELATING TO GENERAL ASSEMBLY -- COMMITTEES AND STAFF
Introduced By: Senators Burke, Ciccone, and Pearson
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 22-6 of the General Laws entitled "Committees and Staff" is hereby
2 amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 22-6-16. Nonprofit funding transparency.
4 (a) Any nonprofit entity that receives grants or other funding in excess of fifty thousand
5 dollars ($50,000) from the general assembly directly or appropriated through the state budget for
6 any fiscal year shall, within ninety (90) days of the receipt of the grant or appropriation, provide
7 information relating to employee compensation within the nonprofit entity to the general assembly.
8 (b) The nonprofit entity shall disclose the total benefit package paid to the five (5) highest
9 compensated employees with reportable compensation of at least one hundred thousand dollars
10 ($100,000) from the organization during the previous fiscal year. This disclosure shall include a
11 description of the position, the total salary or compensation paid along with all benefits provided
12 including, but not limited to, health insurance, retirement or pension contributions, and any other
13 allowances for items such as automobiles, lodging or communication devices. Provided, however,
14 the name of the individual employee need not be disclosed.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
