EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO GENERAL ASSEMBLY -- COMMITTEES AND STAFF
***
1 This act would require any nonprofit that receives grants or other funding from the general
2 assembly in excess of fifty thousand ($50,000) dollars to provide certain information relating to
3 employee compensation of the previous year's five (5) highest compensated employees with
4 reportable compensation of at least $100,000 to the general assembly, as a condition for requesting
5 state funds from the general assembly.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
